Here's a step-by-step walk-through of creating the project directory structure and integrating React, Node.js, MongoDB, and Tailwind CSS:

1. Create the main project directory:

   ```
   mkdir my-website
   cd my-website
   ```

2. Create the React app inside the main project directory:

   ```
   npx create-react-app frontend
   cd frontend
   ```

3. Set up Tailwind CSS in the React app:

   a. Install the required packages:

      ```
      npm install tailwindcss@latest postcss@latest autoprefixer@latest
      ```

   b. Create a `tailwind.config.js` file in the `frontend` folder:

      ```
      npx tailwindcss init
      ```

   c. Open the `tailwind.config.js` file and add the following contents:

      ```js
      module.exports = {
        purge: ['./src/**/*.{js,jsx,ts,tsx}', './public/index.html'],
        darkMode: false,
        theme: {
          extend: {},
        },
        variants: {
          extend: {},
        },
        plugins: [],
      }
      ```

   d. Create a `postcss.config.js` file in the `frontend` folder:

      ```
      touch postcss.config.js
      ```

   e. Open the `postcss.config.js` file and add the following contents:

      ```js
      module.exports = {
        plugins: [
          require('tailwindcss'),
          require('autoprefixer'),
        ],
      }
      ```

   f. Open `src/index.css` and add the following code:

      ```css
      @tailwind base;
      @tailwind components;
      @tailwind utilities;
      ```

   g. Make sure `src/index.js` imports `index.css`. Uncomment or add this line:

      ```javascript
      import './index.css';
      ```

4. Set up the backend folder inside the main project directory:

   ```
   cd ..
   mkdir backend
   cd backend
   ```

5. Initialize a new `package.json` file in the `backend` folder:

   ```
   npm init -y
   ```

6. Install necessary packages for the backend:

   ```
   npm install express cors mongoose dotenv
   ```

7. Create a new file named `server.js` in the `backend` folder and add the following contents:

   ```javascript
   const express = require('express');
   const cors = require('cors');
   const mongoose = require('mongoose');
   const dotenv = require('dotenv');

   dotenv.config();

   const app = express();
   const port = process.env.PORT || 5000;

   app.use(cors());
   app.use(express.json());

   const uri = process.env.ATLAS_URI;
   mongoose.connect(uri, { useNewUrlParser: true, useCreateIndex: true, useUnifiedTopology: true });

   const connection = mongoose.connection;
   connection.once('open', () => {
     console.log('MongoDB database connection established successfully');
   });

   app.listen(port, () => {
       console.log(`Server is running on port: ${port}`);
   });
   ```

8. Set up MongoDB:

   a. Create a MongoDB Atlas account and obtain your connection string as described in the previous setup guide.

   b. In the `backend` directory, create a `.env` file and add your MongoDB connection string:

      ```
      ATLAS_URI=your_connection_string_here
      ```

9. Switch to the main project directory:

   ```
   cd ..
   ```

10. To run both the frontend and backend, install the "concurrently" package:

    ```
    npm install concurrently
    ```

11. Open the `package.json` file inside the `frontend` folder and add the following scripts:

    ```json
    "scripts": {
      "start": "react-scripts start",
      "build": "react-scripts build",
      "test": "react-scripts test",
      "eject": "react-scripts eject",
      "backend": "cd ../backend && npm install && node server.js",
      "dev": "concurrently \"npm start\" \"npm run backend\""
    },
    ```

    The `dev` script configuration now runs both the frontend and backend in parallel.

12. Now you can run both the frontend and backend with a single command:

    ```
    cd frontend
    npm run dev
    ```

You've now successfully set up a project with React, Tailwind CSS, Node.js, and MongoDB, with separate folders for frontend and backend inside the main project directory.

I'll walk you through adding the Tailwind Starter Kit to your project and creating the described Homepage.

1. First, download the Tailwind Starter Kit repository as a ZIP file using the GitHub page. Extract the ZIP file and locate the `assets` folder containing `css`, `js`, and `img` folders.

2. Copy the `assets` folder into your `frontend/src` folder in your project.

3. Open `frontend/src/assets/css/tailwind.css`, copy all the content, and paste this content into your `frontend/src/index.css` file, below the tailwind directives:

   ```css
   @tailwind base;
   @tailwind components;
   @tailwind utilities;

   /* PASTE CONTENTS HERE */
   ```

4. Import the necessary reference files from the `assets` folder into your `frontend/src/index.js`:

   ```javascript
   import "./assets/css/main.css";
   import "./assets/js/main.js";
   ```

5. Create your components based on the Tailwind Starter Kit design:

   a. In the `frontend/src` folder, create a `components` folder.

   b. Inside the `components` folder, create the following components:

      - `Header.js`
      - `HeroSection.js`
      - `WhatWeDoSection.js`
      - `Footer.js`

6. Start designing the Homepage using the components. Add the code below to the respective component files:

   a. `Header.js`:

```javascript
import React from "react";

const Header = () => {
  return (
    <header className="flex items-center justify-between p-6 bg-blue-600">
      {/* Logo */}
      <div className="text-white">LOGO</div>

      {/* Profile Icon/ Sign up / Sign in */}
      <div className="text-white">Sign up / Sign in</div>

      {/* Hamburger Icon */}
      <button className="text-white lg:hidden">
        <i className="fas fa-bars"></i>
      </button>

      {/* Sidebar */}
      <nav className="hidden lg:block">
        <ul className="flex space-x-4">
          <li className="text-white">Link 1</li>
          <li className="text-white">Link 2</li>
          <li className="text-white">Link 3</li>
        </ul>
      </nav>
    </header>
  );
};

export default Header;
```

   b. `HeroSection.js`:

```javascript
import React from "react";
import heroImage from "../assets/img/hero.svg";

const HeroSection = () => {
  return (
    <section className="flex items-center justify-between p-6">
      {/* SVG Image */}
      <img src={heroImage} alt="Hero" />

      {/* Text on the right */}
      <div>
        <h1 className="text-xl font-bold">Heading</h1>
        <p>Description text</p>
      </div>
    </section>
  );
};

export default HeroSection;
```

   c. `WhatWeDoSection.js`:

```javascript
import React from "react";

const WhatWeDoSection = () => {
  return (
    <section className="p-6">
      <h2 className="text-xl font-bold mb-4">What We Do</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Step 1</li>
        <li>Step 2</li>
        <li>Step 3</li>
      </ul>
    </section>
  );
};

export default WhatWeDoSection;
```

   d. `Footer.js`:

```javascript
import React from "react";

const Footer = () => {
  return (
    <footer className="bg-blue-600 p-6 text-white">
      {/* Logo */}
      <div>LOGO</div>

      {/* Hyperlinks */}
      <div>
        <a href="#" className="text-white">Link 1</a>
        <a href="#" className="text-white ml-4">Link 2</a>
      </div>

      {/* Contact Us Form */}
      <form>
        <label htmlFor="email">Email</label>
        <input type="email" id="email" className="ml-2" />
        <button type="submit" className="ml-2">Submit</button>
      </form>

      {/* Copyright */}
      <div className="mt-4">&copy; 2021 Company Name. All rights reserved.</div>
    </footer>
  );
};

export default Footer;
```

7. Import the components and use them in the `frontend/src/App.js`:

```javascript
import React from "react";
import Header from "./components/Header";
import HeroSection from "./components/HeroSection";
import WhatWeDoSection from "./components/WhatWeDoSection";
import Footer from "./components/Footer";

function App() {
  return (
    <div className="App">
      <Header />
      <HeroSection />
      <WhatWeDoSection />
      <Footer />
    </div>
  );
}

export default App;
```

8. Now run the application with `npm run dev` in the `frontend` folder.

You've now successfully added the Tailwind Starter Kit, created several components, and designed a Homepage using these components. Note that you will need to adapt the styling as needed to match your desired design.

To create an index page using React, Tailwind CSS, and components from Notus React, follow these steps:

1. Start with the previously created React and Tailwind CSS setup.

2. Download the Notus React UI Kit from the Creative Tim (https://www.creative-tim.com/product/notus-react) and extract the ZIP file.

3. From the extracted Notus React folder, copy the `assets` folder and paste it into your project's `frontend/src` directory.

4. Open `assets/css/tailwind.css`, copy its content, and paste it in your project's `frontend/src/index.css` file, below the default Tailwind CSS directives:

   ```css
   @tailwind base;
   @tailwind components;
   @tailwind utilities;

   /* PASTE CONTENTS HERE */
   ```

5. Import the necessary reference files from the `assets` folder into your `frontend/src/index.js`:

   ```javascript
   import "./assets/css/main.css";
   import "./assets/js/main.js";
   ```

6. To create and customize components from the Notus React UI Kit, follow the documentation provided in the template and extract sample code from the components in `src/views`.

7. For this example, I provide a basic template for the features you described. 

   Create the following shared components in the `frontend/src/components` folder:

- `src/components/Header.js`
- `src/components/Sidebar.js`
- `src/components/HeroSection.js`
- `src/components/WhatWeDoSection.js`
- `src/components/Footer.js`

8. Add the code for these components as described below:

```javascript
// Header.js
import React from "react";

const Header = () => {
  return (
    <header className="bg-blue-500 p-6">
      <div className="container mx-auto">
        <div className="flex items-center justify-between">
          <div className="text-white">LOGO</div>
          <div className="text-white">
            <i className="fas fa-user-circle"></i>
            {" "}
            Profiles / Sign Up
          </div>
          <button className="text-white lg:hidden">
            <i className="fas fa-bars"></i>
          </button>
        </div>
      </div>
    </header>
  );
};

export default Header;
```

```javascript
// Sidebar.js
import React, { useState } from "react";

const Sidebar = () => {
  const [isOpen, setIsOpen] = useState(false);

  const toggleSidebar = () => {
    setIsOpen(!isOpen);
  };

  return (
    <>
      <button
        onClick={toggleSidebar}
        className="text-white fixed top-6 left-6 z-50"
      >
        <i className="fas fa-bars"></i>
      </button>
      <nav
        className={`fixed top-0 left-0 w-64 h-full bg-blue-500 p-4 z-40 transition-all duration-300 ${
          isOpen ? "translate-x-0" : "-translate-x-full"
        }`}
      >

      </nav>
    </>
  );
};

export default Sidebar;
```

